Description: Fragment of floor of Attic black-glazed pottery open vase, perhaps bowl. Very fine make. Glazed save for central disc on underside, which has two slight mouldings. On floor, frieze of linked palmettes between rings of impressed tongues. Incised inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1867)
